          "type": "incorrect_translation",
          "description": "The translation 'yaradan zaman' (while creating) implies the user is the one creating the file, whereas the English 'on creation' refers to the system process/event. More importantly, 'soruşmayın' is a formal/plural imperative ('do not ask'), which sounds like a command to the user rather than a setting description. In UI contexts for checkboxes, the translation should describe the action/state (e.g., 'Don't ask again') rather than commanding the user.",
